cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes stochastic networks with different classes of requests and routing policies. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the capacity of nodes in the network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper analyzes a dynamical system. 
- cs.PF (Probability) is relevant as the paper deals with Markov processes and their invariant distribution. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the convergence of a rescaled Markov process to a deterministic dynamical system.
